</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Crunch">Crunch</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/crunch" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">crunch</a> is one of the most widely known abdominal exercises in the fitness world. All levels of lifters, beginner to advanced, utilize the crunch and its variations to <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31373978/#:~:text=Traditional%20crunch%20produced%20greater%20or%20similar%20EMG%20activity%20in%20the%20abdominal%20muscles%20and%20minimized%20RF%20activity%20compared%20to%20the%205%2Dminute%20Shaper%20device%2C%20hence%2C%20traditional%20crunch%20is%20preferred%20for%20training%2C%20especially%20for%20individuals%20with%20weak%20abdominal%20musculature%20and%20lower%20back%20problems." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">strengthen their core</a> muscles. Even though it is a <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7345922/#:~:text=The%20greatest%20activity%20in%20the%20RA%2C%20EO%2C%20and%20ES%20muscles%20was%20found%20in%20free%2Dweight%20exercises.%20The%20greatest%20IO%20activity%20was%20found%20in%20core%20stability%20exercises%2C%20while%20traditional%20exercises%20showed%20the%20greatest%20MUL%20activation." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">free-weight exercise</a>, it can positively impact core strength and produce improvements in stability and balance.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Lifters can integrate the crunch into their gym sessions, at the park, or even while lying in bed. It requires no equipment and little space to perform, giving individuals easy access to improvements in health and fitness. To increase the intensity of this exercise, grab a weight at the gym or a large textbook at home.&nbsp;</p>



